Madrid Invests EUR 200 Million in Digital Infrastructure Plan 2024-2027

MADRID, January 2024 - The Community of Madrid has announced a EUR 200 million investment plan to strengthen the region's position as Southern Europe's leading digital hub.

Key initiatives:
1. New fiber optic backbone connecting all municipalities (EUR 80M)
2. Support for data center construction in the Henares Corridor (EUR 60M)
3. Digital skills training program for 50,000 workers (EUR 35M)
4. Smart city pilot projects in 15 municipalities (EUR 25M)

"Madrid already hosts 65% of Spain's data center capacity. This investment will ensure we remain competitive with Amsterdam, Frankfurt, and Dublin," said the Regional Minister for Digital Transformation.

Full coverage at https://noticias.madrid/infraestructura-digital-2024

