Subject: ENISA Cloud Security Certification Scheme: Public consultation opens
Date: Mon, 08 Jan 2024 15:00:00 +0100
Message-ID: <en028@enisa.example>
X-Gmail-Labels: Inbox,Cloud,Security,Important
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8

Dear stakeholders,

ENISA invites comments on the draft European Cloud Security Certification Scheme (EUCS).

The scheme defines three assurance levels:
- Basic: Self-assessment against baseline controls
- Substantial: Third-party audit of technical controls
- High: Comprehensive audit including sovereignty requirements

Key sovereignty provisions in the "High" level:
1. Data must remain within the EU/EEA at all times
2. Operations managed by EU citizens/residents
3. No foreign government access provisions
4. Company ownership must not be subject to foreign control
5. All subcontractors must meet the same requirements

Public consultation period: January 30 - March 15, 2024
Submit comments: https://enisa.example/eucs-consultation

The final scheme is expected to be adopted by Q3 2024.

ENISA Communications

