Dear stakeholders,

The proposed European Digital Infrastructure Act contains several key provisions affecting cloud providers:

1. MINIMUM CONNECTIVITY STANDARDS
   - All EU citizens to have access to 1 Gbps by 2030
   - 5G coverage in all populated areas by 2030

2. CLOUD INFRASTRUCTURE REQUIREMENTS
   - At least 3 EU-based cloud providers per member state by 2027
   - Government data must be stored in EU-sovereign infrastructure
   - Mandatory interconnection between national clouds

3. SUSTAINABILITY MANDATES
   - New data centers must achieve PUE below 1.3
   - 100% renewable energy by 2030
   - Waste heat recovery plans mandatory for facilities above 1MW

4. INVESTMENT FRAMEWORK
   - EUR 10B in EU funding for digital infrastructure
   - Tax incentives for green data centers
   - Fast-track permitting for strategic digital projects

Attached: Q1 2024 infrastructure status report.

EU Digital Infrastructure Directorate
