Executive Team,

Following our quarterly review, here are our multi-cloud strategy recommendations:

CURRENT STATE:
- AWS: 55% of workloads (primary)
- Azure: 30% (secondary, mainly Microsoft ecosystem)
- European provider: 15% (sovereign/regulated workloads)

RECOMMENDED CHANGES FOR 2024:

1. Increase European cloud allocation to 25%
   Rationale: European Data Act compliance, client requirements
   Timeline: Gradual migration Q2-Q4 2024
   Cost impact: +5% initially, break-even by Q3 2025

2. Implement cloud-agnostic abstraction layer
   Technology: Terraform + Crossplane
   Benefit: Reduce provider lock-in, faster migrations
   Investment: EUR 200K in tooling and training

3. Establish GPU cloud strategy
   Need: AI/ML workloads growing 300% YoY
   Options: AWS (p5 instances), CoreWeave, European GPU cloud
   Recommendation: Split between AWS and European provider

4. FinOps program expansion
   Current waste estimate: 22% of cloud spend
   Target: Reduce to 10% by year-end
   Savings: EUR 1.2M annually

Full analysis document shared via the internal portal.

Cloud Strategy Team

