Subject: Sovereign Cloud Stack 6.0 Release Announcement
Date: Thu, 25 Jan 2024 05:00:00 +0100
Message-ID: <en046@oscf.example>
X-Gmail-Labels: Inbox,Cloud
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8

Dear community,

We are pleased to announce the release of Sovereign Cloud Stack (SCS) 6.0.

SCS is an open-source cloud computing stack designed for European digital sovereignty.

KEY FEATURES IN 6.0:
- OpenStack 2024.1 (Caracal) integration
- Kubernetes 1.29 cluster API
- GAIA-X compliance out of the box
- Improved federation support between SCS installations
- Hardware security module (HSM) integration
- Automated compliance reporting for EUCS and C5

ADOPTERS:
- 12 European cloud providers now run SCS in production
- 3 German state governments use SCS for their cloud
- Evaluation ongoing in Spain, France, and Poland

GET STARTED:
Documentation: scs.community/docs
GitHub: github.com/SovereignCloudStack
Community chat: chat.scs.community

This release was made possible by contributions from 45 developers across 15 organizations.

Open Source Cloud Foundation

