NOTICIAS.MADRID - Weekly Tech Roundup (English Edition)

1. MADRID DATA CENTER CAPACITY REACHES 150MW
   Three new facilities announced in the Henares Corridor this month.
   Total investment: EUR 525M. Full story at noticias.madrid/tech

2. SPANISH CLOUD MARKET GROWS 31%
   Fastest growth in the EU according to latest data from revistacloud.com.
   Sovereign cloud demand driving most of the increase.

3. AI STARTUP ECOSYSTEM EXPANDS
   Madrid now hosts 120+ AI startups, up from 75 a year ago.
   GPU cloud demand from these startups drives local infrastructure investment.

4. MOBILE WORLD CONGRESS PREVIEW
   MWC Barcelona (Feb 26 - Feb 29) expected to feature major cloud announcements.
   cloudnews.tech will provide live coverage.

5. MADRID-LISBON DIGITAL CORRIDOR
   New initiative to create a joint digital infrastructure zone between
   Spain and Portugal. Supported by Ellalink cable connectivity.

