<h2>CSA EU Chapter: 2024 Cloud Security Priorities</h2>
<h3>Top Threats to Cloud Computing 2024:</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Misconfiguration and inadequate change control</strong> - Still #1 after 3 years</li>
<li><strong>Identity and access management failures</strong> - Growing with multi-cloud</li>
<li><strong>Insecure APIs and interfaces</strong> - Supply chain attacks via APIs</li>
<li><strong>AI-powered attacks</strong> - NEW: adversarial ML, deepfake social engineering</li>
<li><strong>Data sovereignty violations</strong> - Unintended cross-border data flows</li>
</ol>
<h3>Priority Actions for EU Cloud Providers:</h3>
<table border="1" cellpadding="8" style="border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr><th>Priority</th><th>Action</th><th>Deadline</th></tr>
<tr><td>Critical</td><td>NIS2 compliance preparation</td><td>Oct 2024</td></tr>
<tr><td>High</td><td>EUCS certification readiness</td><td>Q4 2024</td></tr>
<tr><td>High</td><td>Zero Trust architecture adoption</td><td>Ongoing</td></tr>
<tr><td>Medium</td><td>AI security framework implementation</td><td>2025</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Full report: <a href="https://csa.example/eu-threats-2024">csa.example/eu-threats-2024</a></p>
</body></html>
